Sentencas: High-performance metal supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFC) with an integrated high entropy alloy (HEA) internal reforming catalyst (IRC) are demonstrated for transportation applications using ethanol and methanol as fuels.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: Addition of the HEA IRC dramatically improves cell performance and stability when using ethanol/water blend fuel.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: Absence of carbon deposition predicted by thermodynamic calculations is confirmed by Raman spectroscopy analysis of posttest anodes.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: Optimal catalyst processing (deposition technique, loading, firing temperature) and cell operation conditions (flow rates, temperature, fuel compositions) are explored.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: Infiltrated HEA reforming catalyst provides a highly porous structure and low catalyst loading (6 mg cm-2).
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: The designed structure and catalysts achieve small mass transport resistances in the fuel electrode (26.2 s m-1) and oxygen electrode (41.6 s m-1).
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: The best ethanol concentration (60:40 v% ethanol: water) provides 0.83 W cm- 1
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: at 700 degrees C, without carbon deposition.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: The ethanol-fueled MS-SOFC is operated for 500 h, including five thermal cycles.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst

Sentencas: Cell evolution is similar to that reported previously for hydrogen fuel; nickel aggregation and chromia deposition were the major observed changes, and carbon formation can be avoided even after long-term operation.
Titulo: Ethanol-fueled metal supported solid oxide fuel cells with a high entropy alloy internal reforming catalyst
